==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fort
<hw>Fort</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., from <ets>fort</ets>
strong, L. <ets>fortis</ets>; perh. akin to Skr. <ets>darh</ets> to fix,
make firm, and to E. <ets>firm</ets> Cf. <er>Forte</er>, <er>Force</er>,
<er>Fortalice</er>, <er>Comfort</er>, <er>Effort</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Mil.)</fld> <def>A strong or fortified place; usually, a small
fortified place, occupied only by troops, surrounded with a ditch,
rampart, and parapet, or with palisades, stockades, or other means of
defense; a fortification.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Detached works, depending solely on their own strength, belong to
the class of works termed <qex>forts</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Farrow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fortalice</ent>⟦br⟧
